This article discusses the efforts made by President Obama and his administration to reset and improve relations with Russia. It highlights various government-to-government agreements and accomplishments, such as the signing of the New START Treaty, cooperation on addressing the Iran nuclear issue, joint efforts in countering North Korea's nuclear activities, and progress in the area of non-proliferation. The article also mentions collaboration in areas such as Afghanistan, Kyrgyzstan, Georgia, energy efficiency, innovation, and trade and investment. Furthermore, it discusses the promotion of universal values and engagement with Russian civil society, as well as the positive shift in Russian attitudes towards the United States. The article concludes by mentioning efforts to preserve the historical legacy between the two countries.